version_description: Improved layout and overall tuning of instrument along with different position so the player doesn't have to tune down 1/2 step.
Tab more organized. Easier to follow and chords more accurate
Changed some of the standard chords into minor 7th and major 7th chords for added musical colour.
Original key is F# major, so just play open chords in F major with capo on fret 1.
Nobody has done this tab yet and I think I got it quite accurate.
It is a different chord progression from other tabs and it sounds really good.
The other tab is not complete. Enjoy.
